COUNTER-STRIKE GCF
About the Game

Few games today equate the popularity, influence and legacy of the first Counter-Strike game. Counter-Strike is one of those games that helped popularize their genre – is, after all, one of the most classic first-person shooters. After he started out as a Half-Life, Counter-Strike soon took his own life. And it has become so popular that now it’s even played professionally in specialty tournaments. Much of the appeal comes from the basic setting: terrorists fight anti-terrorist units in a series of mission rounds, and the player who chooses the team to be part of. That means you can either plant or defuse bombs, escort VIPs or kidnap them, save hostages or keep them under your control – it’s your choice. The mission can be won either by accomplishing mission goals or by eliminating all team members. What’s more, the stakes are very high on every round: if your character dies in the round, you’re dead. Do not hurt yourself and then heal you miraculously, do not get into the life as soon as you were killed. You’re dead. Until, of course, the round ends and another begins. Talent, intelligence, tactics, quick reflexes – all of these things are essential to survive and thrive in the Counter-Strike world.
